# Copy this file to .devcontainer/.env (gitignored) and fill it in before opening
# the container. The devcontainer loads this file via `--env-file`, so the values
# are injected at run time and never baked into the image or git. post-create.sh
# fails fast if the secrets below aren't set correctly.

# --- Claude auth: provide EXACTLY ONE of the two below ---
# Don't set both: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY outranks CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN, so a
# stale/disabled key silently overrides a valid subscription token. Use one and
# COMMENT OUT the other line (a blank value can still be treated as "set").
#
# Option 1 — Console API key (pay-per-token billing):
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
#
# Option 2 — Pro/Max subscription OAuth token. Generate on a machine with a
# browser via `claude setup-token` (prints a ~1-year token), then paste it here
# and comment out the ANTHROPIC_API_KEY line above:
# CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=

# --- GitHub auth (always required) ---
# Auth for the `gh` CLI so the agent can open PRs. Use a FINE-GRAINED PAT scoped
# to only the repo(s) the sandbox should touch (Contents + Pull requests,
# read/write), with a short expiry — a broad classic PAT in a bypass-permissions
# sandbox has a large blast radius.
GH_TOKEN=
